reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;"><strong>Were you concerned about Biden running for reelection in 2024?=
=C2=A0</strong>
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;margin-bottom:0px;">When I got to the White House, I was starry-eyed. I=E2=
=80=99d wanted to work in the White House since I was 5 years old, when I m=
emorized the presidents from a place mat. And it was incredible to be there=
=2E I used to drive my boss home every=20=
night, my chief of staff, because we l=
ived in the same building, and I remember him saying something about, =E2=
=80=9CWell, <em>that=E2=80=99s</em> after the reelect. That=E2=80=99s a sec=
ond term
[issue].=E2=80=9D I said, =E2=80=9CWait, <em>what</em>?=E2=80=9D</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;"><strong>So you believed Biden when he said he would be a =E2=80=
=9Cbridge.=E2=80=9D</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">It wasn=E2=80=99t that I=
 believed in =E2=80=9Cthe bridge.=E2=80=9D I just assumed=E2=80=94kind of l=
ike <strong>Barack Obama</strong> probably assumed. I figured that by 2024,=
 this was going to be, =E2=80=9COkay, we=E2=80=99re going to pass the torch
to another generation of Democrats, and let <em>them</em> handle a Trump 2.=
0 campaign.=E2=80=9D But I was brought to reality pretty fast. Like, =E2=80=
=9CWhy not? Why <em>wouldn=E2=80=99t</em> he run?=E2=80=9D They were kind o=
f either stuck with him, or they were eating their vegetables and saying, =
=E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s our best shot. Not a socialist from Vermont. We=E2=80=
=99re comfortable with him, he=E2=80=99s competent, he=E2=80=99s earned a l=
ot of goodwill.=E2=80=9D Ultimately, the problem with deciding to run again=
 was a misread of our mandate. When Biden was elected,
we lost 13 House seats.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Who was driving the ree=
lect? Was it Jill or White House staffers who wanted to hold on to power?=
=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><br/>Jill would=
 be the first person in her convertible driving to the beach, and she=E2=80=
=99d never have a reason to come back to D.C. She wants only what <em>he</e=
m> wants, and that=E2=80=99s how their lives have always been. But what
<em>really</em> got under their skin was the media and other Democrats ques=
tioning whether he should run again. Every time there was a story about his=
 age, or whether he could do another election, or whether he should be the =
candidate, they just doubled down. They felt, =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve proved=
 everybody wrong in the past. Obama tried to push him out of the 2016 campa=
ign=E2=80=94not once, but twice. Nobody thought we=E2=80=99d win the nomina=
tion. Nobody thought he could beat an incumbent.=E2=80=9D To them, this was=
 another
example of everyone underestimating them.<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Keeping him away from the press was a way to c=
over up his condition.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The president=E2=80=99s=
 team was scared to death of impromptu, unscripted, unrehearsed, unpractice=
d, unchoreographed <em>anything</em>. They couldn=E2=80=99t compete in the =
attention economy. They didn=E2=80=99t have any idea how. And they didn=E2=
=80=99t have the
vessel in Biden, who would have done anything. He <em>loves</em> TV. He lov=
es doing stuff. It was the orbit that didn=E2=80=99t trust the candidate.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;">Biden needed the press, but when he needed the press the most, the=
y didn=E2=80=99t trust him. And then the press put their foot on the gas an=
d never took it off, and he was politically dead in a month.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
